Just doing an image search with your favorite search engine for "X-Men Wolfsbane" will lead you down a very deep rabbit hole. She has a normal human form, and various artists in different comics have drawn her as everything from a fuzzy-faced werewolf woman with a hairdo that is strongly reminiscent of pointy wolf ears, to a doggo girl with a pointy snoot and a fluffy tail, all in official "canon" Marvel material. She was introduced in the 80s and every few years gets a new set of powers, a new appearance, a new retroactive continuity, because comics.

And if you don't like doggo girls, Marvel also has Catseye, who is an honest-to-god catgirl. Depending on the writer, the series, and the year, she may believe herself to be a cat who can temporarily turn human, or an alien, rather than the human mutant with cat powers she actually is. In human form she sometimes retains her cat tail. She's kind of cute. Of course, this being Marvel, the cute catgirl must suffer horribly, be persecuted and misunderstood, etc., etc. Thank you Chris Claremont.
